<DOC><DOCNO> AP890519-0114 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-19-89 1413EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Korea-Bonus     05-19 0152</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Korea-Bonus,0155</SECOND><HEAD>North Korea Says it Will Pay Special Bonus to Workers</HEAD><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   North Korea said Friday it will pay a bonus to allworkers, technicians and office employees in June before the 13thWorld Festival of Youth and Students opens in Pyongyang in July.   The bonus of 100 percent of regular monthly wages would be paidunder a decree adopted Thursday by the Central People's Committee,according to official Korean Central News Agency, monitored inTokyo.   The bonus will be paid ``in appreciation of the feats performedby the working class and other laboring people in the past 200-daycampaigns,'' the report said.   The youth festival with an anti-imperialist theme will be heldin the North Korean capital July 1-8. Officials say 30,000 peoplefrom more than 170 countries are expected for the festival, a majorpolitical, cultural and sports event involving mostly communist andThird World nations.</TEXT></DOC>